{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I study how the brain processes"},{"time":2000,"text":"information. That is, how it takes"},{"time":4000,"text":"information in from the outside world, and"},{"time":6000,"text":"converts it into patterns of electrical activity,"},{"time":8000,"text":"and then how it uses those patterns"},{"time":10000,"text":"to allow you to do things --"},{"time":12000,"text":"to see, hear, to reach for an object."},{"time":14000,"text":"So I'm really a basic scientist, not"},{"time":16000,"text":"a clinician, but in the last year and a half"},{"time":18000,"text":"I've started to switch over, to use what"},{"time":20000,"text":"we've been learning about these patterns"},{"time":22000,"text":"of activity to develop prosthetic devices,"},{"time":25000,"text":"and what I wanted to do today is show you"},{"time":27000,"text":"an example of this."},{"time":29000,"text":"It's really our first foray into this."},{"time":31000,"text":"It's the development of a prosthetic device"},{"time":33000,"text":"for treating blindness."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35000,"text":"So let me start in on that problem."},{"time":37000,"text":"There are 10 million people in the U.S."},{"time":39000,"text":"and many more worldwide who are blind"},{"time":41000,"text":"or are facing blindness due to diseases"},{"time":43000,"text":"of the retina, diseases like"},{"time":45000,"text":"macular degeneration, and there's little"},{"time":47000,"text":"that can be done for them."},{"time":49000,"text":"There are some drug treatments, but"},{"time":51000,"text":"they're only effective on a small fraction"},{"time":53000,"text":"of the population. And so, for the vast"},{"time":55000,"text":"majority of patients, their best hope for"},{"time":57000,"text":"regaining sight is through prosthetic devices."},{"time":59000,"text":"The problem is that current prosthetics"},{"time":61000,"text":"don't work very well. They're still very"},{"time":63000,"text":"limited in the vision that they can provide."},{"time":65000,"text":"And so, you know, for example, with these"},{"time":67000,"text":"devices, patients can see simple things"},{"time":69000,"text":"like bright lights and high contrast edges,"},{"time":71000,"text":"not very much more, so nothing close"},{"time":73000,"text":"to normal vision has been possible."}]},{"cues":[{"time":76000,"text":"So what I'm going to tell you about today"},{"time":78000,"text":"is a device that we've been working on"},{"time":80000,"text":"that I think has the potential to make"},{"time":82000,"text":"a difference, to be much more effective,"},{"time":84000,"text":"and what I wanted to do is show you"},{"time":86000,"text":"how it works. Okay, so let me back up a"},{"time":88000,"text":"little bit and show you how a normal retina"},{"time":90000,"text":"works first so you can see the problem"},{"time":92000,"text":"that we were trying to solve."},{"time":94000,"text":"Here you have a retina."},{"time":96000,"text":"So you have an image, a retina, and a brain."},{"time":98000,"text":"So when you look at something, like this image"},{"time":100000,"text":"of this baby's face, it goes into your eye"},{"time":102000,"text":"and it lands on your retina, on the front-end"},{"time":104000,"text":"cells here, the photoreceptors."},{"time":106000,"text":"Then what happens is the retinal circuitry,"},{"time":108000,"text":"the middle part, goes to work on it,"},{"time":110000,"text":"and what it does is it performs operations"},{"time":112000,"text":"on it, it extracts information from it, and it"},{"time":114000,"text":"converts that information into a code."},{"time":116000,"text":"And the code is in the form of these patterns"},{"time":118000,"text":"of electrical pulses that get sent"},{"time":120000,"text":"up to the brain, and so the key thing is"},{"time":122000,"text":"that the image ultimately gets converted"},{"time":124000,"text":"into a code. And when I say code,"},{"time":126000,"text":"I do literally mean code."},{"time":128000,"text":"Like this pattern of pulses here actually means \"baby's face,\""},{"time":131000,"text":"and so when the brain gets this pattern"},{"time":133000,"text":"of pulses, it knows that what was out there"},{"time":135000,"text":"was a baby's face, and if it"},{"time":137000,"text":"got a different pattern it would know"},{"time":139000,"text":"that what was out there was, say, a dog,"},{"time":141000,"text":"or another pattern would be a house."},{"time":143000,"text":"Anyway, you get the idea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":145000,"text":"And, of course, in real life, it's all dynamic,"},{"time":147000,"text":"meaning that it's changing all the time,"},{"time":149000,"text":"so the patterns of pulses are changing"},{"time":151000,"text":"all the time because the world you're"},{"time":153000,"text":"looking at is changing all the time too."},{"time":156000,"text":"So, you know, it's sort of a complicated"},{"time":158000,"text":"thing. You have these patterns of pulses"},{"time":160000,"text":"coming out of your eye every millisecond"},{"time":162000,"text":"telling your brain what it is that you're seeing."},{"time":164000,"text":"So what happens when a person"},{"time":166000,"text":"gets a retinal degenerative disease like"},{"time":168000,"text":"macular degeneration? What happens is"},{"time":170000,"text":"is that, the front-end cells die,"},{"time":172000,"text":"the photoreceptors die, and over time,"},{"time":174000,"text":"all the cells and the circuits that are"},{"time":176000,"text":"connected to them, they die too."},{"time":178000,"text":"Until the only things that you have left"},{"time":180000,"text":"are these cells here, the output cells,"},{"time":182000,"text":"the ones that send the signals to the brain,"},{"time":184000,"text":"but because of all that degeneration"},{"time":186000,"text":"they aren't sending any signals anymore."},{"time":188000,"text":"They aren't getting any input, so"},{"time":190000,"text":"the person's brain no longer gets"},{"time":192000,"text":"any visual information --"},{"time":194000,"text":"that is, he or she is blind."}]},{"cues":[{"time":197000,"text":"So, a solution to the problem, then,"},{"time":199000,"text":"would be to build a device that could mimic"},{"time":201000,"text":"the actions of that front-end circuitry"},{"time":203000,"text":"and send signals to the retina's output cells,"},{"time":205000,"text":"and they can go back to doing their"},{"time":207000,"text":"normal job of sending signals to the brain."},{"time":209000,"text":"So this is what we've been working on,"},{"time":211000,"text":"and this is what our prosthetic does."},{"time":213000,"text":"So it consists of two parts, what we call"},{"time":215000,"text":"an encoder and a transducer."},{"time":217000,"text":"And so the encoder does just"},{"time":219000,"text":"what I was saying: it mimics the actions"},{"time":221000,"text":"of the front-end circuitry -- so it takes images"},{"time":223000,"text":"in and converts them into the retina's code."},{"time":225000,"text":"And then the transducer then makes the"},{"time":227000,"text":"output cells send the code on up"},{"time":229000,"text":"to the brain, and the result is"},{"time":231000,"text":"a retinal prosthetic that can produce"},{"time":234000,"text":"normal retinal output."},{"time":236000,"text":"So a completely blind retina,"},{"time":238000,"text":"even one with no front-end circuitry at all,"},{"time":240000,"text":"no photoreceptors,"},{"time":242000,"text":"can now send out normal signals,"},{"time":244000,"text":"signals that the brain can understand."},{"time":247000,"text":"So no other device has been able"},{"time":249000,"text":"to do this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":251000,"text":"Okay, so I just want to take"},{"time":253000,"text":"a sentence or two to say something about"},{"time":255000,"text":"the encoder and what it's doing, because"},{"time":257000,"text":"it's really the key part and it's"},{"time":259000,"text":"sort of interesting and kind of cool."},{"time":261000,"text":"I'm not sure \"cool\" is really the right word, but"},{"time":263000,"text":"you know what I mean."},{"time":265000,"text":"So what it's doing is, it's replacing"},{"time":267000,"text":"the retinal circuitry, really the guts of"},{"time":269000,"text":"the retinal circuitry, with a set of equations,"},{"time":271000,"text":"a set of equations that we can implement"},{"time":273000,"text":"on a chip. So it's just math."},{"time":275000,"text":"In other words, we're not literally replacing"},{"time":278000,"text":"the components of the retina."},{"time":280000,"text":"It's not like we're making a little mini-device"},{"time":282000,"text":"for each of the different cell types."},{"time":284000,"text":"We've just abstracted what the"},{"time":286000,"text":"retina's doing with a set of equations."},{"time":288000,"text":"And so, in a way, the equations are serving"},{"time":290000,"text":"as sort of a codebook. An image comes in,"},{"time":292000,"text":"goes through the set of equations,"},{"time":295000,"text":"and out comes streams of electrical pulses,"},{"time":297000,"text":"just like a normal retina would produce."}]},{"cues":[{"time":301000,"text":"Now let me put my money"},{"time":303000,"text":"where my mouth is and show you that"},{"time":305000,"text":"we can actually produce normal output,"},{"time":307000,"text":"and what the implications of this are."},{"time":309000,"text":"Here are three sets of"},{"time":311000,"text":"firing patterns. The top one is from"},{"time":313000,"text":"a normal animal, the middle one is from"},{"time":315000,"text":"a blind animal that's been treated with"},{"time":317000,"text":"this encoder-transducer device, and the"},{"time":319000,"text":"bottom one is from a blind animal treated"},{"time":321000,"text":"with a standard prosthetic."},{"time":323000,"text":"So the bottom one is the state-of-the-art"},{"time":325000,"text":"device that's out there right now, which is"},{"time":327000,"text":"basically made up of light detectors,"},{"time":329000,"text":"but no encoder. So what we did was we"},{"time":331000,"text":"presented movies of everyday things --"},{"time":333000,"text":"people, babies, park benches,"},{"time":335000,"text":"you know, regular things happening -- and"},{"time":337000,"text":"we recorded the responses from the retinas"},{"time":339000,"text":"of these three groups of animals."},{"time":341000,"text":"Now just to orient you, each box is showing"},{"time":343000,"text":"the firing patterns of several cells,"},{"time":345000,"text":"and just as in the previous slides,"},{"time":347000,"text":"each row is a different cell,"},{"time":349000,"text":"and I just made the pulses a little bit smaller"},{"time":351000,"text":"and thinner so I could show you"},{"time":354000,"text":"a long stretch of data."}]},{"cues":[{"time":356000,"text":"So as you can see, the firing patterns"},{"time":358000,"text":"from the blind animal treated with"},{"time":360000,"text":"the encoder-transducer really do very"},{"time":362000,"text":"closely match the normal firing patterns --"},{"time":364000,"text":"and it's not perfect, but it's pretty good --"},{"time":366000,"text":"and the blind animal treated with"},{"time":368000,"text":"the standard prosthetic,"},{"time":370000,"text":"the responses really don't."},{"time":372000,"text":"And so with the standard method,"},{"time":375000,"text":"the cells do fire, they just don't fire"},{"time":377000,"text":"in the normal firing patterns because"},{"time":379000,"text":"they don't have the right code."},{"time":381000,"text":"How important is this?"},{"time":383000,"text":"What's the potential impact"},{"time":385000,"text":"on a patient's ability to see?"},{"time":388000,"text":"So I'm just going to show you one"},{"time":390000,"text":"bottom-line experiment that answers this,"},{"time":392000,"text":"and of course I've got a lot of other data,"},{"time":394000,"text":"so if you're interested I'm happy"},{"time":396000,"text":"to show more. So the experiment"},{"time":398000,"text":"is called a reconstruction experiment."},{"time":400000,"text":"So what we did is we took a moment"},{"time":402000,"text":"in time from these recordings and asked,"},{"time":405000,"text":"what was the retina seeing at that moment?"},{"time":407000,"text":"Can we reconstruct what the retina"},{"time":409000,"text":"was seeing from the responses"},{"time":411000,"text":"from the firing patterns?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":413000,"text":"So, when we did this for responses"},{"time":416000,"text":"from the standard method and from"},{"time":419000,"text":"our encoder and transducer."},{"time":421000,"text":"So let me show you, and I'm going to"},{"time":423000,"text":"start with the standard method first."},{"time":425000,"text":"So you can see that it's pretty limited,"},{"time":427000,"text":"and because the firing patterns aren't"},{"time":429000,"text":"in the right code, they're very limited in"},{"time":431000,"text":"what they can tell you about"},{"time":433000,"text":"what's out there. So you can see that"},{"time":435000,"text":"there's something there, but it's not so clear"},{"time":437000,"text":"what that something is, and this just sort of"},{"time":439000,"text":"circles back to what I was saying in the"},{"time":441000,"text":"beginning, that with the standard method,"},{"time":443000,"text":"patients can see high-contrast edges, they"},{"time":445000,"text":"can see light, but it doesn't easily go"},{"time":447000,"text":"further than that. So what was"},{"time":449000,"text":"the image? It was a baby's face."},{"time":452000,"text":"So what about with our approach,"},{"time":454000,"text":"adding the code? And you can see"},{"time":456000,"text":"that it's much better. Not only can you"},{"time":458000,"text":"tell that it's a baby's face, but you can"},{"time":460000,"text":"tell that it's this baby's face, which is a"},{"time":462000,"text":"really challenging task."},{"time":464000,"text":"So on the left is the encoder"},{"time":466000,"text":"alone, and on the right is from an actual"},{"time":468000,"text":"blind retina, so the encoder and the transducer."},{"time":470000,"text":"But the key one really is the encoder alone,"},{"time":472000,"text":"because we can team up the encoder with"},{"time":474000,"text":"the different transducer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":476000,"text":"This is just actually the first one that we tried."},{"time":478000,"text":"I just wanted to say something about the standard method."},{"time":480000,"text":"When this first came out, it was just a really"},{"time":482000,"text":"exciting thing, the idea that you"},{"time":484000,"text":"even make a blind retina respond at all."},{"time":487000,"text":"But there was this limiting factor,"},{"time":490000,"text":"the issue of the code, and how to make"},{"time":492000,"text":"the cells respond better,"},{"time":494000,"text":"produce normal responses,"},{"time":496000,"text":"and so this was our contribution."},{"time":498000,"text":"Now I just want to wrap up,"},{"time":500000,"text":"and as I was mentioning earlier"},{"time":502000,"text":"of course I have a lot of other data"},{"time":504000,"text":"if you're interested, but I just wanted to give"},{"time":506000,"text":"this sort of basic idea"},{"time":508000,"text":"of being able to communicate"},{"time":511000,"text":"with the brain in its language, and"},{"time":513000,"text":"the potential power of being able to do that."},{"time":516000,"text":"So it's different from the motor prosthetics"},{"time":518000,"text":"where you're communicating from the brain"},{"time":520000,"text":"to a device. Here we have to communicate"},{"time":522000,"text":"from the outside world"},{"time":524000,"text":"into the brain and be understood,"},{"time":526000,"text":"and be understood by the brain."}]},{"cues":[{"time":528000,"text":"And then the last thing I wanted"},{"time":530000,"text":"to say, really, is to emphasize"},{"time":532000,"text":"that the idea generalizes."},{"time":534000,"text":"So the same strategy that we used"},{"time":536000,"text":"to find the code for the retina we can also"},{"time":538000,"text":"use to find the code for other areas,"},{"time":540000,"text":"for example, the auditory system and"},{"time":542000,"text":"the motor system, so for treating deafness"},{"time":544000,"text":"and for motor disorders."},{"time":546000,"text":"So just the same way that we were able to"},{"time":548000,"text":"jump over the damaged"},{"time":550000,"text":"circuitry in the retina to get to the retina's"},{"time":552000,"text":"output cells, we can jump over the"},{"time":554000,"text":"damaged circuitry in the cochlea"},{"time":556000,"text":"to get the auditory nerve,"},{"time":558000,"text":"or jump over damaged areas in the cortex,"},{"time":560000,"text":"in the motor cortex, to bridge the gap"},{"time":563000,"text":"produced by a stroke."}]},{"cues":[{"time":565000,"text":"I just want to end with a simple"},{"time":567000,"text":"message that understanding the code"},{"time":569000,"text":"is really, really important, and if we"},{"time":571000,"text":"can understand the code,"},{"time":573000,"text":"the language of the brain, things become"},{"time":575000,"text":"possible that didn't seem obviously"},{"time":577000,"text":"possible before. Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":579000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}